The paper discusses the development of a simulator for reversible computing, which falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET). The focus of the paper is on the implementation of digital circuits, which is related to the sub-category of Architecture (cs.AR). The use of reversible logic blocks for design and implementation is a key aspect of the paper, which is related to the sub-category of Digital Circuits (cs.DC). The development of new algorithms for Truth Table generation and symmetry analysis is related to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the use of a GUI-based simulator and the emphasis on user-friendliness is related to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO).
